Abstract = {{In the footwear sector, automation is often performed by robotic arms
   due to the inherent adaptive requirements of some of its tasks. With the
   Industry 4.0 revolution, automation is even less human dependent than
   before. The fact that fewer people interact with machinery during the
   manufacturing process has led to a rising need for production
   monitoring. The interconnection of machines present in 4.0 environments
   makes monitoring possible at a low investment cost. In this paper, a
   common communication layer is proposed to enable homogeneous status data
   retrieval of robotic arms from several different robot manufacturers.
   This layer is then attached to a 3D simulator software as a client,
   responsible for the monitoring process. Experiments proved the
   feasibility of the proposed method in a test bench scenario applying the
   required constraints of time, cost, bandwidth and disk space.}},
