   network service layer across different tiers. Using probabilistic
   analysis models, we prove the efficiency of the proposed hierarchical
   fog computing compared with the flat architecture. In this paper, IIoT
   data and requests are divided into both high priority and low priority
   requests; the high priority requests are urgent/emergency demands that
   need to be scheduled rapidly. Therefore, we use two-priority queuing
   model in order to schedule and analyze IIoT data. Finally, we further
   introduce a workload assignment algorithm to offload peak loads over
   higher tiers of the fog hierarchy. Using realistic industrial data from
   Bosch group, the benefits of the proposed architecture compared to the
