Number = {{8}},
Pages = {{3701-3711}},
Month = {{AUG}},
Abstract = {{In recent years, two technologies, the cloud computing and the Internet
   of Things (loT), have a synergistic effect in the modern organizations
   as digitization is a new business trend for various industries.
   Therefore, many organizations outsource their crowdsourced
   industrial-IoT (IIoT) data in the cloud system to reduce data management
   overhead. However, data authentication is one of the fundamental
   security/trust requirements in such IIoT network. The certificateless
   signature (CLS) scheme is a cryptographic primitive that provides data
   authenticity in IIoT systems. Recently, CLS has become a prime research
   focus due to its ability to solve the key-escrow problem in a very
   recent identity-based signature technique. Many CLS schemes have already
   been developed using map-to-point (MTP) hash function and random oracle
   model (ROM). However, due to the implementation difficulty and
   probabilistic nature of MTP function and ROM, those CLSs are
   impractical. Hence, the development of a CLS for lightweight devices
   mounted in IIoT has become one of the most focused research trends. This
   paper presents a new pairingbased CLS scheme without MTP function and
   ROM. The new CLS scheme is secure against both the Type-I and Type-II
   adversaries under the hardness of extended bilinear strong
   Diffie-Hellman (BSDH) and BSDH assumptions, respectively. Performance
   evaluation and comparison proves that our scheme outperforms other CLS
   schemes.}},
