Abstract = {{Remanufacturing is the process of bringing end-of-life products back to
   good-as-new. It plays a critical role in decoupling economic growth from
   growth in resource use, and in accelerating the circular economy.
   However, the uptake of remanufacturing activities faces obstacles. This
   paper reviews the challenges encountered by the remanufacturing sector
   and discusses how the Industry 4.0 revolution could help to effectively
   address these issues and unlock the potential of remanufacturing. Two
