Abstract = {{The advent of Industry 4.0 is expected to dramatically change the
   manufacturing industry as we know it today. Highly standardized, rigid
   manufacturing processes need to become self-organizing and
   decentralized. This flexibility leads to new challenges to the
   management of smart factories in general and production planning and
   control in particular. In this contribution, we illustrate how
   established techniques from Business Process Management (BPM) hold great
   potential to conquer challenges in Industry 4.0. Therefore, we show
   three application cases based on the DFKI-Smart-Lego-Factory, a fully
   automated ``smart factory{''} built out of LEGO (R) bricks, which
   demonstrates the potentials of BPM methodology for Industry 4.0 in an
   innovative, yet easily accessible way. For each application case
   (model-based management, process mining, prediction of manufacturing
   processes) in a smart factory, we describe the specific challenges of
   Industry 4.0, how BPM can be used to address these challenges, and,
   their realization within the DFKI-Smart-Lego-Factory.}},
