Abstract = {{In this age of digital disruption, every industry is undergoing digital
   transformation and manufacturing is no exception. Since
   Internet-of-Things (IoT) and Big Data have immense transformational
   potential, manufacturing companies are in a race to implement IoT-based
   solutions to innovate, improve productivity, reduce costs, and improve
   their market share. As companies try to embrace IoT, one of the key
   challenges that they face is to come up with an ``Integrated
   Approach.{''} ``Integrated Approach{''} includes fitting IoT in the
   overall system landscape, selecting the right use case, and evaluating
   and deciding on implementation approach. This paper provides guidance to
   transform legacy manufacturing unit to a smart factory conforming to
   Industry 4.0 principles. It presents a reference architecture and offers
   various practical approaches for consideration to embark on digital
   journey. It details each approach along with its own benefits and
   challenges and helps organizations to realistically determine faster
   time-to-market versus its long-term goals. This paper attempts to
   perform a deep dive on various aspects of integrated approach which will
   be immensely helpful for organizations and researchers alike.}},
