Abstract = {{The rapid pace of technological developments played a key role in the
   previous industrial revolutions. However, the fourth industrial
   revolution (Industry 4.0) and its embedded technology diffusion progress
   is expected to grow exponentially in terms of technical change and
   socioeconomic impact. Therefore, coping with such transformation require
   a holistic approach that encompasses innovative and sustainable system
   solutions and not just technological ones. In this article, we propose a
   framework that can facilitate the interaction between technological and
   social innovation to continuously come up with pro-active, and hence
   timely, sustainable strategies. These strategies can leverage economic
   rewards, enrich society at large, and protect the environment. The new
   forthcoming opportunities that will be generated through the next
   industrial wave are gigantic at all levels. However, the readiness for
   such revolutionary conversion require coupling the forces of
   technological innovation and social innovation under the sustainability
   umbrella.}},
