Abstract = {{Power generation increasingly relies on decentralised and interconnected
   computerised systems. Concepts like ``Industrial Internet of Things{''}
   of the Industrial Internet Consortium (IIC), and ``Industry 4.0{''} find
   their way in this strategic industry. Risk of targeted exploits of
   errors and vulnerabilities increases with complexity, interconnectivity
   and decentralization. Inherently stringent security requirements and
   features make nuclear computerised applications and systems a benchmark
   for industrial counterparts seeking to hedge against those risks.
   Consequently, this contribution presents usual cyber security
