   required for an effective design process for distributed control
   systems. The following work details the implementation of the IEC-61499
   standard in low-cost devices using 4DIAC-FORTE for distributed control
   of a FESTO MPS 200 educational system, by using Unified Modeling
   Language (UML) diagrams as a software tool for modeling the function
   blocks (FBs) of the IEC-61499 standard. This work demonstrates a simple
