   of IIoT devices raises a number of security concerns, because the IIoT
   device is weak in defending against malware, and the method of managing
   a large number of IIoT devices is awkward and inconvenient. This article
   proposes a multi-level DDoS mitigation framework (MLDMF) to defend
   against DDoS attacks for IIoT, which includes the edge computing level,
   fog computing level, and cloud computing level. Software defined
   networking is used to manage a large number of IIoT devices and to
   mitigate DDoS attacks in IIoT. Experimental results show the
